## Task Summary: Move CLI business logic to usecase/infrastructure layers

**Track:** track-plan-activation-2026-03-14
**Task:** T008 — CLI 層に残ったビジネスロジックを適切なレイヤーへ移動する
**Date:** 2026-03-15

### Changes

- libs/usecase/src/track_resolution.rs: new module — resolve_track_id_from_branch, resolve_transition, reject_branchless_implementation_transition with tests
- libs/usecase/src/worktree_guard.rs: new module — parse_dirty_worktree_paths, validate_clean_worktree with tests
- libs/infrastructure/src/track/fs_store.rs: added FsTrackStore::find_with_meta and standalone read_track_metadata
- apps/cli/src/commands/track/resolve.rs: delegates branch parsing and metadata reads to usecase/infra
- apps/cli/src/commands/track/transition.rs: delegates resolve_transition and branchless guard to usecase
- apps/cli/src/commands/track/activate.rs: delegates worktree parsing/validation to usecase
- apps/cli/src/commands/track/mod.rs: removed unused imports (TaskStatusKind, TaskTransition, codec)

### Why

CLI layer had accumulated business logic (branch name parsing, transition resolution, activation guards, worktree validation) that belongs in usecase/infrastructure per hexagonal architecture. Moving these functions to proper layers improves testability and maintains the usecase→domain only dependency constraint.
